  "prompt": "In what year was Indian currency released with Mahatma Gandhi's photo on it?",
  "response": "Mahatma Gandhi's portrait was first featured on Indian currency notes in **1996**. This change was part of an effort by the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) to incorporate national leaders and symbols that resonate with the country's heritage and values. Since 1996, Gandhi's image has been prominently displayed on several denominations, including \u20b950, \u20b9100, \u20b9500, and \u20b92000 notes, becoming an integral part of India's currency design.\n\n**Key Points:**\n- **Year Introduced:** 1996\n- **Authority:** Reserve Bank of India (RBI)\n- **Denominations:** Initially \u20b950, \u20b9100, \u20b9500, and later others\n- **Purpose:** To reflect national heritage and honor Mahatma Gandhi's legacy\n\nThis move not only honored Gandhi's role in India's independence but also aimed to instill a sense of national pride among citizens through everyday items like currency.",
